Noun

1. ''[[chemistry]]'' '''destruction by chemical action''' a process by which something, especially a metal, is destroyed progressively by chemical action, as iron when it rusts

----

2. '''corroded material''' material produced by corrosion, e.g. rust.

----

3. '''gradual destruction''' the gradual destruction or undermining of something
   -a steady corrosion of the public trust
----

4. '''result of corrosion''' the condition produced by corrosion

also see: [[corrosible]]